
#Installing modules on windows:
A.Normal install-
steps:
1.Download package(source it from web)
2.Copy to packages folder(where all modules are present)(or not doesnt matter),unzip if needed
3.Point on package folder hold shift+rt click>>open command window here
4.Enter setup.py install

B.pip install:
steps:
1.cmd
2.pip install <packagename>
or
c:/python36/scripts/pip install <packagename>
#to upgrade:c:/python36/scripts/pip install --upgrade <packagename>
or
download package(http://www.lfd.uci.edu/~gohlke/pythonlibs/)
point on package folder shift+rt click>>open command window here
c:/python36/scripts/pip install "<filename.whl>"

#upgrading pip
1.cmd
2.python -m pip install --upgrade pip

C.Using easy install
steps:
1.cmd
2.easy_install <packagename>
